<paragraph id="082436BFFFC3FFECBF152BAF43D60C8F" blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBF152BAF41D00CE4" box="[312,437,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Etymology</emphasis>
: This species is named for Dr. R. R. Askew, who has contributed substantially to our knowledge of European 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBD3D2B9743CA0C8F" authorityName="Dalman" authorityYear="1820" box="[784,943,1204,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pteromalidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="082436BFFFC3FFECBF152BFF42B20DD7" blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBF152BFF41F60CB4" box="[312,403,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Biology</emphasis>
: Unknown; like other species from this genus, 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBDE42BFF445B0CB4" authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[969,1086,1244,1269]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBDE42BFF445B0CB4" box="[969,1086,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21DC57D6FFC3FFECBA6A2BFF44E20CB7" box="[1095,1159,1244,1270]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is probably a parasitoid of a certain species of 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBCA52A2742850D5F" box="[648,736,1284,1310]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
(in this case probably a species of moderate size). All the individuals were swept on steppe vegetation at Valea lui David Natural Reserve. More than 500 species of angiosperms were identified here, the 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBA6A2A7744C20D2F" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[1095,1191,1364,1390]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
being the dominant species (
<bibRefCitation id="6C0A4B4EFFC3FFECBFCF2A5F42AF0DD7" author="Mititelu, D. &amp; Motiu, T. &amp; TeSu, C. &amp; Vitalariu, C." box="[482,714,1404,1430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" pagination="81 - 100" refId="ref7555" refString="Mititelu, D., Motiu, T., D a sc a lescu, D., TeSu, C., Vitalariu, C. (1969) Flora Si vegetatia pajiStilor &quot; Valea lui David &quot; IaSi. Studii S i Comunic a ri, Muzeul de S tiin t ele Naturii Bac a u, 81 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1969">Mititelu &amp; al. 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="082436BFFFC3FFE3BF152A8743C609BF" blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1870]" lastBlockId="8.[264,1323,284,510]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBF152A8742FA0DFC" box="[312,671,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBF9C2A8742FA0DFC" authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[433,671,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">Halticoptera askewi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21DC57D6FFC3FFECBC8A2A8742820DFF" box="[679,743,1444,1470]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the group of species with the median area of propodeum distinctly reticulated, together with 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBDFC2AEF449D0DA7" authority="(Curtis)" baseAuthorityName="Curtis" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[977,1272,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdina">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBDFC2AEF44EF0DA4" box="[977,1162,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. smaragdina</emphasis>
(Curtis)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBB232AEF41940E4F" authority="(Dalman)" baseAuthorityName="Dalman" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellana">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBB232AEF41130E4C" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. patellana</emphasis>
(Dalman)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBFD12AD7428D0E4F" authority="(Walker)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[508,744,1524,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBFD12AD7421C0E4C" box="[508,633,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. collaris</emphasis>
(Walker)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBD0D2AD744070E4F" authority="Graham. The" authorityName="Graham. The" authorityYear="1972" box="[800,1122,1524,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatula">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBD0D2AD743A40E4C" box="[800,961,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. elongatula</emphasis>
Graham. The
</taxonomicName>
female and male of 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBF05293F41F90E74" authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[296,412,1564,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBF05293F41F90E74" box="[296,412,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21DC57D6FFC3FFECBF89293F41870E77" box="[420,482,1564,1590]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
would run in Graham’s key (1969) as far as couplet 3 and 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBAB5293F411E0E1F" authority="(Dalman)" baseAuthorityName="Dalman" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellana">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBAB5293F454F0E74" box="[1176,1322,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. patellana</emphasis>
(Dalman)
</taxonomicName>
, on account of its distinctly reticulated propodeum and, in the case of the male, also on account of its small maxillary stipites. From both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBA64294F44D20EC4" baseAuthorityName="Dalman" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[1097,1207,1644,1669]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellana">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBA64294F44D20EC4" box="[1097,1207,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">patellana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this new species differs mainly in having a very transverse petiole, a larger body size and some other characteristic features, which are mentioned below. Some of the characters of 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFC3FFECBAF6299F454F0E94" authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[1243,1322,1724,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFC3FFECBAF6299F454F0E94" box="[1243,1322,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21DC57D6FFC3FFECBF2529C741220EBF" box="[264,327,1764,1790]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are rather uncommon for most of the species in the genus: an almost sessile gaster, OOL much longer than POL, a very distinct frenal groove, and the bottom edge of the toruli slightly above lower edge of eyes. The presence of these characters could question the generic placement of this species. However, other characters i.e. the rounded collar of the pronotum, the slightly asymmetric bidentate margin of the clypeus, the antennal formula, the postmarginal vein which is shorter than the marginal vein and the enlarged male maxillary palpi, do indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFCCFFE3BCE92EB7437109EC" authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[708,788,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFCCFFE3BCE92EB7437109EC" box="[708,788,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21DC57D6FFCCFFE3BD362EB7433C09EF" box="[795,857,404,430]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to genus 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFCCFFE3BA012EB744A709EC" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1811" box="[1068,1218,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFCCFFE3BA012EB744A709EC" box="[1068,1218,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Halticoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I do not think it is appropriate to create a new subgenus for 
<taxonomicName id="CF9B4D3CFFCCFFE3BD812E9F43990994" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[940,1020,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi">
<emphasis id="3AEFEAADFFCCFFE3BD812E9F43990994" box="[940,1020,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
before examining more material, especially from the Central and East Palearctic.
</paragraph>
